Env var (simplest)JSON config fileUninstall (revert) <p>Tools that read <code>OPENAI_BASE_URL</code> or <code>ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL</code> are already handled by <code>tokenmeter install</code>'s shell patching. A backend adapter for these tools only needs <code>Detect()</code> and <code>Verify()</code>.</p> <pre><code>func (b *Backend) Install() error {
    path := configPath()
    data, _ := os.ReadFile(path)
    var cfg map[string]any
    json.Unmarshal(data, &amp;cfg)
    cfg["baseURL"] = "http://127.0.0.1:4191"
    modified, _ := json.MarshalIndent(cfg, "", "  ")
    return os.WriteFile(path, modified, 0o644)
}
</code></pre> <p>Always store the original value and restore it on uninstall. Do not just delete the key — the tool may need a valid endpoint to function.</p>
